#: ../../modules.rst:7
msgid ""
"A module is a NS8 application which is usually composed of a backend and "
"a frontend. An application backend can contain one or more containers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules.rst:10
msgid ""
"Every time a module instance is added to the cluster, the new instance is"
" named as the module itself followed by a progressive number starting "
"from 1. Given a module named ``myapp``, instances will be named "
"``myapp1``, ``myapp2`` and so on. You can add a more meaningful label to "
"the instance from the software center."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules.rst:15
msgid ""
"Some modules require specific resources that cannot be shared. As an "
"example, the Samba module needs to reserve DNS and SMB well-known TCP "
"ports. You can install only one instance per node of this type of "
"modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules.rst:19
msgid ""
"Modules that don't require exclusive access to resources can be installed"
" multiple times on the same node. As an example, you can install multiple"
" OpenLDAP server on a single node."
msgstr ""

